definition.value: A cephalosporin compound having methoxymethyl and [(2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(hydroxyimino)acetyl]amino side-groups; a third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic.

A cephalosporin compound having (E)-2-{[5,6-dioxo-4-(2-oxoethyl)-1,4,5,6-tetrahydro-1,2,4-triazin-3-yl]sulfanyl}ethenyl and [(2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetyl]amino side-groups; a third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic.
A flavin mononucleotide that is 8-amino-8-demethylriboflavin in which the hydroxy hydrogen at position 5' of the ribitol fragment has been replaced by a phosphono group.
Any heparin oligosaccharide consisting of 16 glycosidically linked monosaccharide residues.
Any heparin oligosaccharide consisting of 20 glycosidically linked monosaccharide residues.
